This GUI is inspired by the spotitpy implementation for an automatic tool for object based colocalization (https://github.com/alexiaales/SpotitPy?tab=readme-ov-file)
to run the GUI as a CLI, you should define the hyperparameters first to run the colocalization analysis, this is done using the following format:

python /Users/noahwijnheijmer/GUI/Custom_CLI.py \
-i "/Users/noahwijnheijmer/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-HvA/afstuderen/Microscopy Data Huntingtin aggregates/Raw data #1/20240212_CKR_E10B_mHtt-HAQ97doxy48h_BafA1_HA-STAR580_CCCT1-STAR635P_A11-STAR460L_nucspotlive488_3.lif" \
-o /Users/noahwijnheijmer/GUI/results \
-m cyto \
-f 2 \
-u 3 \
--pc1 90 \
--pc2 80 \
-t 5 \
-s 2 \
-w 1 \
-b 15 \
-g 3 \
--auto on

to run the analysis edit the paths to the path on your own device.

## General Settings
| Parameter | Value | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `-i`      | *Path to .lif file* | Input microscopy image |
| `-o`      | *Path to output folder* | Output directory |
| `-m`      | `cyto` | Cytoplasmic mode (optimized for cytoplasmic spot detection) |
| `--auto`  | `on`   | Automated run without manual prompts |

---

## Image Smoothing
| Parameter | Value | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `-f`      | `2`   | Gaussian filter sigma (amount of smoothing) |

---

## Thresholding & Spot Detection
| Parameter | Value | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `-u`      | `3`   | Upper threshold factor (for adaptive thresholding) |
| `--pc1`   | `90`  | First percentile cutoff (bright pixel threshold) |
| `--pc2`   | `80`  | Second percentile cutoff (background suppression) |
| `-t`      | `5`   | Absolute intensity threshold (minimum spot brightness) |

---

## Morphology & Segmentation
| Parameter | Value | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `-s`      | `2`   | Minimum spot size (radius or morphological size) |
| `-w`      | `1`   | Watershed segmentation (enabled to separate touching spots) |

---

## Background Correction & Post-processing
| Parameter | Value | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `-b`      | `15`  | Background correction radius (for background subtraction) |
| `-g`      | `3`   | Gap closing / dilation parameter (spot continuity) |

---

particle size is here set to: 15


	• Works well for medium-sized protein aggregates
	• Keeps sensitivity without overdetecting noise
	• Compatible with TrackPy and wavelet filters used in SpotitPy

If you observe over-segmentation or miss smaller foci, you can later try 11 or 9. For large aggregates, increase to 21 or 25.

to run the GUI, simply also download the GUI.py file and run that in your terminal, for example: python /Users/noahwijnheijmer/Experimentation/GUI/Custom_GUI.py
